<keyLead box="[713,1228,1658,1677]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">– Femora mostly black, pale at apices only.. 13</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="82" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
<paragraph blockId="81.[701,1228,212,1758]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
<keyLead pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
13. Dorsal vestiture erect and dense, fine; male genitalia as in figures 54A–F and 55A– 
<collectionCode box="[1160,1168,1712,1731]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">I</collectionCode>
......................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Knight)" baseAuthorityName="Knight" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[1070,1227,1738,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Slaterocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mohri">
<emphasis box="[1070,1129,1738,1758]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">mohri</emphasis>
(Knight)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
