<keyLead pageId="82" pageNumber="82">
15. Dorsal vestiture long and dense; male genitalia as in figures 54A–F and 55A– 
<collectionCode box="[455,463,453,472]" pageId="82" pageNumber="82">I</collectionCode>
............................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Knight)" baseAuthorityName="Knight" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[463,619,479,499]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Slaterocoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
